### 3. Agent Builder Missing Entity Fields ✅ Designed
**Files:** [agent-builder.ts](file:///Users/torniketsomaia/projects/@tsomaia.tech/ductus/src/interfaces/builders/agent-builder.ts), [default-agent-builder.ts](file:///Users/torniketsomaia/projects/@tsomaia.tech/ductus/src/builders/default-agent-builder.ts), [agent-entity.ts](file:///Users/torniketsomaia/projects/@tsomaia.tech/ductus/src/interfaces/entities/agent-entity.ts)

**Agreed design:**
- Add `scope`, `maxContextTokens`, `maxFailures`, `maxRecognizedHallucinations`, `timeout` fields to `AgentEntity`
- Store them in `DefaultAgentBuilder`, serialize in `[BUILD]()`
- **Lifecycle enforcement via AgentDispatcher** (modernized concept):
  - Created by `createKernel` from flow's `{ agent, model, adapter }[]` tuples
  - Owns adapter registry (agent name → live adapter instance)
  - Exposes: `invoke(agentName, skillName, input): AsyncIterable<AgentChunk>`
  - Internally tracks per-agent ephemeral state: tokens, failures, hallucinations, turns
  - Enforces limits — handles replacement per overflow policy (summarize/truncate/fresh)
  - Directly injected into reaction adapter factory (not via DI — framework internal)
  - **Ephemeral state by design** — lifecycle counters reset on restart, same as UI state. Domain events are persisted via ledger; operational agent state is not.

